</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Dr Vladimir Chernousenko, scientific director of the 20-mile exclusion zone
around Chernobyl, claimed up to 10,000 people died following the 1986
explosion - compared with the official Soviet figure of 31. Meanwhile the
Atomic Energy Authority said up to 40,000 people worldwide may die from
cancer over the next 70 years because of the disaster.
