FT  19 APR 91 / UK Company News: Anglo-Park plans merger
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ANGLO-PARK plans to merge with fellow property group St James Estates via an
agreed offer of 19 new ordinary shares for every 20 St James ordinary not
already held.
Anglo-Park acquired a 21.9 per cent stake in St James in recent weeks and
the offer is for the remaining equity.
It also announced yesterday that its losses jumped to Pounds 1.17m (Pounds
68,000) in the first-half to December 31.
The deficit was swelled by provisions of Pounds 518,000 against book values
of developed and investment properties and a further Pounds 115,000 written
off against revaluation reserves.
Damage was also inflicted by a provision of Pounds 342,000 against the
investment in St James. This is related to a write-down of the value of the
latter's property in Oxford Street, London, following a professional
valuation. The matter is the subject of litigation.
The interim dividend is cut to 0.5p (2p) on losses per share of 12.6p
(0.7p).
Turnover fell to Pounds 247,000 (Pounds 610,000) and gross profit came to
Pounds 3,000 (Pounds 165,000).
For the year St James incurred a loss of Pounds 1.9m on turnover of Pounds
3.15m.
