<HEADLINE>
FT  19 APR 91 / The Lex Column: Slough Estates
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Slough always needed a rights issue to relieve its balance sheet - the
question was when and how much. In the event a convertible looks the
sensible way to limit dilution, though the terms had to be generous and the
Pounds 137m proceeds may not suffice for the longer term. The immediate
effect is to cut gearing to a little over 50 per cent, a figure which could
edge back above 60 per cent this year without asset sales. From the market's
point of view the important thing is that the waiting is over. But the
shares will only prosper with signs that the bottom has been reached in the
industrial property cycle.
</TEXT>
