<HEADLINE>
FT  19 APR 91 / Technology (Worth Watching): Ceramics find their bearings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A TOUGH, lightweight ceramic material is now being made into bearings for a
range of industrial sectors.
Developed by SNR Roulements, in Annecy, France, the bearings are made of
silicon nitride, which is chemically very stable. Other properties of the
material are that it is extremely hard and therefore lasts much longer than
traditional steel bearings.
SNR has two bearings for various applications: hybrid bearings - ceramic
balls held in place by steel rings - to give the speed needed in precision
machine tools; and ceramic bearings for use in nuclear physics and the
petrochemical industry where there are strong chemicals.
SNR Roulements: France, 50 65 30 00.
