FT  18 APR 91 / International Company News: Blackstone in German link-up
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BLACKSTONE Group, the US investment banking boutique, yesterday announced
that it was linking up with Sal. Oppenheim, an old-established private bank
in Germany. Blackstone has already formed similar alliances with Hambro
Magan in the UK, with Banque Indosuez in Paris, and with Nikko Securities in
Japan.
The aim of the latest venture is for the two firms to co-operate on
transatlantic mergers and acquisitions business, and to participate jointly
in investment opportunities in both Germany and the US as principals.
