FT  18 APR 91 / International Company News: Internatio-Mueller plummets
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RONALD VAN DE KROL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   AMSTERDAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
NET PROFITS at Internatio-Mueller, the diversified Dutch transport, trading
and engineering group, plummeted to Fl 2.6m (Dollars 1.38m) in 1990 from Fl
56.1m in 1989, reflecting setbacks in Australia, New Zealand and the port of
