FT  18 APR 91 / Parliament and Politics: National sovereignty
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FURTHER surrenders of national sovereignity by the 12 member states of the
European Community were envisaged by Baron Hermann von Richthofen, the
German Ambassador to London, yesterday.
Responding to questions at a Parliamentary press gallery luncheon he argued
that the pooling of sovereignity which had already occured through the
creation of Nato and the United Nations was likely to continue as the EC
progressed towards economic and monetary union.
Baron von Richthofen saw a further pooling of sovereignity as the inevitable
consequence of the creation of the single European single market.
