FT  18 APR 91 / Fraud case remands
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A VENEZUELAN investment banker and an American financial consultant were
remanded in custody for a week at Marlborough Street Court in London
yesterday, charged in connection with an alleged plot to defraud a merchant
bank out of a Pounds 425,000 loan. Mr Adrian Simionescu-Marin and Mr Ronald
Conquest are accused of conspiring with others between April 10 and 15 to
defraud Merrill Lynch, Pierce, Fenner and Smith.
