<HEADLINE>
FT  18 APR 91 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Prices paid for wool at Australian auctions continue to move gradually
upwards. The market indicator reached 467 this week, nearly 10pc above its
recent low point. Wool auctioned in other countries is also meeting with
good trade demand, and occasional mention of purchases by China, Russia, and
Eastern Europe are encouraging. There is however no clear recovery from the
textile recession which coincided with the wool crisis. In the UK activity
is no worse but hopes of an all-round improving trend are certainly not
being rapidly realised. Prices remain competitive for this reason and only
just reflect raw wool's strength.
</TEXT>
