FT  18 APR 91 / The Lex Column: PSBR
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Yesterday's UK public sector borrowing requirement figures for March are a
little worrying given that the recession looks likely to haunt the Treasury
for some time yet. But bearing in mind that the Pounds 8bn deficit projected
on Budget day looked out of date even then, the implications for government
funding should not be exaggerated. With the British Telecom stake flotation
up its sleeve, the government has plenty of room for manoeuvre. Its biggest
concern might be the pressure placed on institutional liquidity by the
competing demands of gilts, rights issues and give-away privatisation
shares.
</TEXT>
